Excerpts: American GrownIntroductionOn March 20, 2009, I was like any other hopeful gardener with a pot out on the windowsill or a small plot by the back door.
The garden was also being planted on a historic landscape: the South Lawn of the White House.
Page 19And over the past three years, our White House Kitchen Garden has bloomed into so much more.
Our White House Kitchen Garden is just one of thousands of gardens across this country, each with a story worth telling.
Reprinted from American Grown: The Story of the White House Kitchen Garden and Gardens Across America by Michelle Obama.